<HEADLINE>
ACER PRODUCTS RECEIVE RED DOT 2007 AWARDS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, May 3 (CNA) 05/03/07  19:25:12 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
Acer Corp's Aspire L350 desktop computer, Ferrari 1000 notebook,
and C500 handheld, have received the internationally renowned Red
Dot Award for their stylish design and good quality, an Acer
spokesman said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the Red Dot Award is sponsored by the
Design Zentrum Nordrhein Westfalen of Germany to recognize
oustanding industrial design.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the award ceremony will take place June 25 in
Germany and that Acer's winning products will be exhibited in the
Red Dot design museum.
</P>
<P>
A total of 523 products have won this award, which has a history
of more than 50 years. The jury evaluated 2,548 submissions from
43 countries according to criteria such as innovation,
functionality, ergonomics,  formal quality and environmental
protection,  the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The award-winning Aspire L350 is a miniature multimedia desktop
of merely three liters in volume and has enhanced acoustic and
thermal solutions that create quieter and more stable operation.
</P>
<P>
The 12-inch wide Ferrari 1000 notebook has many Ferrari racecar
elements in its design, such as highly resilient carbon-fiber
material, "foot pedal" touchpad buttons and dashboard-like
lights, the spokesman said, adding that it has also won a
Japanese G-Mark Good Design Award.
</P>
<P>
The C500 handheld is a full-featured personal digital assistant
with built-in Global Positioning System and a slim and clean-cut
formal look that allowed it to also win a German iF product
design award, the spokesman said.
</P>
